text:
Media-type declarations are not honoured via either of the two mechanisms:

<?xml-stylesheet type="text/css" href="css" media="..." ?>
or in-line

@media whatever {
  ....
}
For example, declarations with media="print" are used when viewing on screen,
and declarations with media="screen" are used when printing.

There seems to be code in Batik to handle media selection, but it seems as
though the client never specifies the list of media which it should recognise.
